cted due to stale remote ref — no fetch/update before push | Stages: taskify:completed, plan:completed, build:completed, verify:completed, review:completed, review-fix:completed, ship:failed","createdAt":"2026-04-10T16:17:53.227Z","wordCount":963,"positions":[0,7,14,21,29,34,50,59,68,85,94,108,115,122,134,144,148,153,160,166,173,181,189,197,205,210,221,234,247,254,260,270,278,288,297,307,321,329,344,359,366,374,383,397,408,419,424,438,454,468,479,486,498,505,509,515,522,528,533,544,549,557,563,571,582,588,595,601,611,623,635,647,654,662,668,677,686,689,697,702,709,716,721,729,736,747,753,760,764,769,778,785,791,798,804,807,813,820,827,834,842,850,861,866,877,883,894,901,912,919,930,937,941,952,957]},"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"build\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"AuthService (Payload-based PBKDF2) is the correct auth mechanism for login endpoints, not UserStore — they are not interchangeable.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Route handlers in this project live at src/app/(frontend)/api/ not src/app/api/ — the (frontend) segment matters for routing.\",\"scope\":\"src/app\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"API handlers follow a standard middleware chain: withAuth HOC → rate-limiter → handler, all returning Result<T, E>.\",\"scope\":\"API handlers\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Input validation uses Zod schemas imported from src/validation/ at the API boundary before any service calls.\",\"scope\":\"src/validation\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:10:47.655Z","wordCount":715,"positions":[2,10,18,31,38,47,54,67,75,81,96,104,109,123,129,140,144,165,169,188,196,205,212,225,232,238,255,263,271,275,280,290,295,299,303,307,319,329,337,349,360,368,372,380,387,400,407,411,420,429,438,449,456,465,471,476,486,499,509,525,533,537,550,557,570,577,583,594,599,603,611,625,629,648,652,661,668,672,680,689,697,701]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Register route instantiates AuthService and payloadInstance but never uses them — falls back to old UserStore utility, violating task requirements\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"When a task requires using AuthService (PBKDF2) over a legacy utility, adding dead code that looks correct will pass a casual review but fail correctness checks\",\"scope\":\"auth implementation\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Always verify the call chain — confirming AuthService is instantiated is insufficient; confirm it is actually invoked in the request path\",\"scope\":\"code review\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:13:08.271Z","wordCount":655,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,64,70,83,99,119,125,137,143,151,155,165,174,184,189,204,212,216,220,224,229,238,244,251,258,267,281,286,295,301,314,322,329,336,345,352,357,367,373,386,393,400,411,416,428,437,445,450,469,476,485,492,499,510,515,523,534,549,565,579,593,602,617,625,632,640,645]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"In the register route, authService and payloadInstance were instantiated but never used — the handler only called registerUser from payload directly. Always audit that every injected dependency is act\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When a route handler imports both a service class and a singleton instance (e.g. payload), confirm which is actually called in the handler body — dead imports silently compile but cause runtime misbeh\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Payload singleton is used directly as `payload` in route handlers (not injected via a container). When adding auth service dependencies, prefer consistent instantiation per-handler invocation rather t\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Rate limiting middleware (next()) and Zod validation were confirmed as the project's standard approach for auth route hardening, matc","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:36:49.877Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,66,75,82,98,119,136,142,153,161,166,173,191,199,209,216,233,242,256,262,270,274,278,282,287,296,302,309,316,325,339,345,353,361,368,376,388,398,413,423,440,449,463,471,478,483,491,500,512,518,526,535,543,547,551,555,560,569,575,582,589,602,609,617,630,635,648,660,666,676,680,689,695,712,719,724,732,746,753,764,778,782,790,801,812,820,824,828,832,842,849,860,867,872,881,893,905,909,925,942,952,961,974,979,985,996]},"ep_stage_diary_004":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_004","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Refresh tokens must never be returned in the JSON response body — always send them via HttpOnly cookies to prevent XSS exfiltration.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When fixing a security pattern (e.g. moving tokens to HttpOnly cookies), audit all similar endpoints to apply the fix consistently.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:37:52.013Z","wordCount":380,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,63,70,75,84,100,105,114,121,128,138,142,151,162,170,174,190,198,207,214,223,235,244,253,267,274,284,293,303,313,321,334,344,348,364,372]},"ep_stage_diary_005":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_005","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"login route had security issue with refresh token - must use HttpOnly cookie, not JSON body response (same fix as register route)\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/login/route.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"A fix applied to register (HttpOnly cookie) must be mirrored to login - when copying a pattern, audit all instances for the same issue\",\"scope\":\"auth endpoints\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Review-fix stage must close ALL critical findings before approval; partial fixes don't meet bar\",\"scope\":\"review process\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:45:03.459Z","wordCount":573,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,59,65,75,84,95,103,111,116,120,129,137,141,146,151,161,166,173,182,191,199,203,207,211,216,222,228,235,242,251,260,264,275,285,294,302,310,322,335,345,354,364,382,387,395,403,408,422,429,442,449,456,460,466,471,481,490,499,506,516,524,530,536,541,547,555,562]},"ep_stage_diary_006":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_006","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Register endpoint omits firstName/lastName (required:true in Payload Users), causing 500 on every registration in production. Integration tests mask this because they mock payload.create without field\",\"scope\":\"src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When mocking payload.create in tests, always validate the fields passed to it, otherwise required-field gaps go undetected until production.\",\"scope\":\"testing\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Payload CMS collections may have required fields beyond the obvious; always inspect the collection definition before writing create() calls.\",\"scope\":\"src/server/payload\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:48:02.725Z","wordCount":691,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,64,73,79,89,99,108,116,124,132,140,153,169,181,193,199,209,222,227,235,242,250,258,266,270,274,278,283,292,298,305,312,321,333,341,349,359,366,373,386,393,407,417,426,432,437,440,451,457,471,479,491,498,511,518,526,530,551,560,567,578,587,594,606,617,628,635,643,652,661,669,673,680]}},"totalDocs":7}